The paper focuses on developing a new system for querying big graphs, which involves designing a computing model that can effectively utilize cluster resources for processing light-workload graph queries. This work is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including database systems (cs.DB), distributed computing (cs.DC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), information retrieval (cs.IR), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
